## Theorem: mathd_numbertheory_45

Theorem: mathd_numbertheory_45
Prove: (nat.gcd 6432 132) + 11 = 23

Goal: (nat.gcd 6432 132) + 11 = 23

## English proof (from stage 1)
{
  "key_observation": "Compute the gcd by applying the Euclidean algorithm: 6432 is divisible by 132 with remainder 48, and then gcd(132, 48) reduces to gcd(48, 36), which is 12.",
  "plan": [
    "Apply the Euclidean algorithm to reduce gcd(6432, 132) to a smaller gcd.",
    "Continue reducing until the gcd is easy to compute.",
    "Evaluate the resulting gcd explicitly.",
    "Add 11 and simplify to obtain 23."
  ],
  "steps": [
    {
      "claim": "nat.gcd 6432 132 = nat.gcd 132 48.",
      "reasoning": "By the Euclidean algorithm, gcd(a, b) = gcd(b, a mod b). Since 6432 = 132 · 48 + 48, the remainder of 6432 upon division by 132 is 48.",
      "facts_used": [
        "Euclidean algorithm",
        "division algorithm"
      ]
    },
    {
      "claim": "nat.gcd 132 48 = nat.gcd 48 36.",
      "reasoning": "Again using the Euclidean algorithm, gcd(a, b) = gcd(b, a mod b). Since 132 = 48 · 2 + 36, the remainder of 132 upon division by 48 is 36.",
      "facts_used": [
        "Euclidean algorithm",
        "division algorithm"
      ]
    },
    {
      "claim": "nat.gcd 48 36 = 12.",
      "reasoning": "Both 48 and 36 are divisible by 12, and 12 is the greatest common divisor because 48 = 12 · 4 and 36 = 12 · 3, while any common divisor of 48 and 36 must divide their difference 12.",
      "facts_used": [
        "definition of gcd",
        "divisibility",
        "common divisor divides differences"
      ]
    },
    {
      "claim": "nat.gcd 6432 132 = 12.",
      "reasoning": "Combining the equalities from the previous steps gives nat.gcd 6432 132 = nat.gcd 48 36 = 12.",
      "facts_used": [
        "step 1",
        "step 2",
        "step 3"
      ]
    },
    {
      "claim": "(nat.gcd 6432 132) + 11 = 23.",
      "reasoning": "Substituting nat.gcd 6432 132 = 12 yields 12 + 11 = 23.",
      "facts_used": [
        "step 4",
        "arithmetic"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "final_answer": "23"
}

